Name: BULK CARGO WEIGHT IN SHORT TONS IN TENTHS
Explanation: THE WEIGHT OF CARGO THAT IS GENERALLY SHIPPED IN VOLUME WHERE THE TRANSPORTATION CONVEYANCE IS THE ONLY EXTERNAL CONTAINER
Version: SUCH AS LIQUIDS, ORE, OR GRAIN MEASURED IN SHORT TONS TO THE NEAREST TENTH.

Name: OVERSIZE CARGO WEIGHT IN SHORT TONS IN TENTHS
Explanation: THE WEIGHT OF CARGO THAT EXCEEDS THE USABLE DIMENSION OF THE 436L PALLET, 104" X 84" X 96", OR A HEIGHT SET BY THE PARTICULAR MODEL AIRCRAFT TO THE NEAREST TENTH.

Name: OUTSIZE CARGO WEIGHT IN SHORT TONS IN TENTHS
Explanation: {IT: REPLACEMENT FUDN FOR CURRENT FUDN 4. ADDED WORD "WEIGHT" TO BE CONSISTEN WITH FFIRN NAME.}THE WEIGHT OF CARGO THAT EXCEEDS 1090" X 117" X 105"
Version: THAT IS, TOO LARGE FOR A C-130, C-141 OR SIMILAR SIZE AIRCRAFT, TO THE NEAREST TENTH.
